Pathological fixture members are NOT committed in static form. They are
materialized at test setup time by test/fixtures/pathological/mkfixtures.sh
(invoked from the e2e SeedSource helper) so that:

  * NFC vs NFD twin filenames survive (some filesystems / git checkouts
    silently normalize one form to the other).
  * Control bytes 0x07 (BEL) and 0x1B (ESC) in filenames are preserved
    (a Windows checkout would refuse them; many editors mangle them).
  * Sparse files retain their sparse-ness (git stores them as fully
    expanded blobs; the sparseness would be lost on checkout).
  * Immutable files (chflags uchg) are settable only at materialization
    time on a real APFS / HFS+ mount; the bit is filesystem state, not
    file content.

See MANIFEST.txt in this directory for the full inventory.
